1
00:00:00,440 --> 00:00:02,110
(Child actors were accompanied
by a guardian...)

2
00:00:02,170 --> 00:00:03,740
(and filmed in a safe,
supervised environment.)

3
00:00:18,220 --> 00:00:20,060
Are you some kind of pervert?

4
00:00:22,460 --> 00:00:24,000
We slept in each other's arms?

5
00:00:24,060 --> 00:00:26,900
Please stop that man!
He's a stalker. A stalker!

6
00:00:28,000 --> 00:00:29,000
Hello, everyone.

7
00:00:29,070 --> 00:00:30,140
(Episode 3)

8
00:00:30,200 --> 00:00:31,200
A pleasure to meet you all.

9
00:00:32,570 --> 00:00:34,140
Nice to meet you all.
Yes, it's great to meet you.

10
00:00:34,710 --> 00:00:35,770
Nice to meet you.

11
00:00:38,280 --> 00:00:39,410
A pleasure to meet you all.

12
00:00:41,850 --> 00:00:42,850
All right!

13
00:00:43,420 --> 00:00:47,220
- It's a pleasure to meet you all.
- Isn't that him from the lobby?

14
00:00:47,290 --> 00:00:49,420
A pleasure to meet you. Yes.

15
00:00:51,490 --> 00:00:52,490
Good to meet you all.

16
00:01:00,300 --> 00:01:02,270
- Please introduce yourself.
- I am so doomed.

17
00:01:06,000 --> 00:01:09,370
Hello.
It is a pleasure to meet you all.

18
00:01:09,910 --> 00:01:12,810
He's a fellow alumnus
from my time in Argentina...

19
00:01:12,910 --> 00:01:17,220
and a former global brand director
who worked throughout South America.

20
00:01:17,520 --> 00:01:18,520
Most recently, he worked...

21
00:01:19,050 --> 00:01:21,620
for the Argentinian meat processor,
Asador,

22
00:01:21,890 --> 00:01:23,790
where he successfully led
their rebranding.

23
00:01:24,460 --> 00:01:27,330
Meat processing? So this industry
isn't his background?

24
00:01:27,660 --> 00:01:29,260
To be perfectly honest,

25
00:01:29,660 --> 00:01:32,060
I don't know the first thing
about fashion or design.

26
00:01:32,400 --> 00:01:35,170
I'm pretty much a layman.

27
00:01:35,930 --> 00:01:39,440
So I'll be counting on all of you
for your support.

28
00:01:39,740 --> 00:01:40,740
All right!

29
00:01:41,870 --> 00:01:43,480
Let's go!

30
00:01:46,040 --> 00:01:47,250
Let's go!

31
00:01:48,410 --> 00:01:50,080
- Let's go!
- Yes.

32
00:01:57,420 --> 00:01:59,320
Oh, Ms. Gong Ju Ah?

33
00:02:00,660 --> 00:02:02,890
- Yes?
- Follow me.

34
00:02:03,730 --> 00:02:04,930
Yes, Director.

35
00:02:18,840 --> 00:02:19,910
Aren't you surprised?

36
00:02:20,180 --> 00:02:24,120
Yes. The office is
quite simple, Director.

37
00:02:24,850 --> 00:02:26,050
I'm not talking about that.

38
00:02:26,850 --> 00:02:28,620
Weren't you surprised to see me?

39
00:02:32,090 --> 00:02:35,890
Why?
Why would I be surprised, Director?

40
00:02:37,300 --> 00:02:41,100
Look at you, playing dumb.
It's me! The pervert stalker!

41
00:02:41,930 --> 00:02:44,440
I don't know what you mean.

42
00:02:44,440 --> 00:02:46,740
I believe this is the first time
we've met, sir.

43
00:02:47,540 --> 00:02:50,840
So that's how
you're going to play it?

44
00:02:53,510 --> 00:02:55,380
Is that my desk?

45
00:02:57,080 --> 00:02:59,580
I need to get to work.

46
00:03:05,460 --> 00:03:07,330
Last Saturday evening, you saw me...

47
00:03:07,760 --> 00:03:10,360
at the chicken soup restaurant
in Ganghwa.

48
00:03:10,360 --> 00:03:11,930
You mistook me for a waiter...

49
00:03:12,000 --> 00:03:13,600
and said, "One soju, please."
And now this?

50
00:03:14,230 --> 00:03:15,500
That wasn't me, Director.

51
00:03:16,130 --> 00:03:18,800
You even fell into the ocean.
When I offered you my hand,

52
00:03:18,870 --> 00:03:20,810
you asked if we were dating.
And now, you don't remember?

53
00:03:21,310 --> 00:03:22,510
I did not, Director.

54
00:03:22,570 --> 00:03:26,280
The samhap at Gaetdari Guesthouse?
You said it was delicious.

55
00:03:26,340 --> 00:03:29,080
- You don't remember that either?
- I do not, Director.

56
00:03:33,180 --> 00:03:34,190
We...

57
00:03:35,590 --> 00:03:37,190
Didn't you say
we slept in each other's arms?

58
00:03:40,020 --> 00:03:41,090
I...

59
00:03:41,930 --> 00:03:44,960
That never happened, Director.
I said no, so if you continue this,

60
00:03:45,030 --> 00:03:47,870
it'll make me uncomfortable.
Please focus on your work.

61
00:03:49,270 --> 00:03:51,900
You startled me. Okay, whatever.

62
00:03:51,970 --> 00:03:54,670
Fine, you don't remember.
Let's just get to work.

63
00:03:59,010 --> 00:04:02,710
Oh, contact HR and get
the design team's staff files.

64
00:04:02,710 --> 00:04:03,720
Pardon?

65
00:04:04,320 --> 00:04:06,320
Yes. One moment. Just a second.

66
00:04:06,380 --> 00:04:10,090
The design team's personnel files...

67
00:04:10,420 --> 00:04:11,490
Is there anything else?

68
00:04:11,590 --> 00:04:15,490
Yes, get the designers' portfolios
and their performance reviews.

69
00:04:15,590 --> 00:04:17,160
Performance reviews.

70
00:04:17,230 --> 00:04:19,100
And bring back the clothes
I lent you that day.

71
00:04:19,100 --> 00:04:22,770
Yes. I've already had them washed,
so I'll bring them in tomorrow...

72
00:04:32,110 --> 00:04:34,380
Right. Of course.

73
00:04:34,710 --> 00:04:37,850
I gave you free food, clothes,
and a place to stay,

74
00:04:38,220 --> 00:04:41,450
and in return, I was treated
like a pervert and a stalker.

75
00:04:41,490 --> 00:04:43,550
And to top it off,
a complete stranger.

76
00:04:45,160 --> 00:04:46,420
I'm sorry.

77
00:04:46,860 --> 00:04:47,860
But...

78
00:04:48,360 --> 00:04:52,500
that was a private incident,
so let's just agree to forget it.

79
00:04:53,600 --> 00:04:57,640
- You really mean that?
- Of course, I do.

80
00:05:03,510 --> 00:05:07,080
Proposals for the design competition
over the last three years...

81
00:05:07,150 --> 00:05:10,350
- Compile them all, selected or not.
- Yes, Director.

82
00:05:10,350 --> 00:05:14,250
Also, organize the FG lookbooks,
ad visuals, and seasonal proposals.

83
00:05:15,190 --> 00:05:16,190
Yes, Director.

84
00:05:23,630 --> 00:05:25,230
(Presidential Candidate
Nomination Petition)

85
00:05:25,300 --> 00:05:29,270
- Here you are, sir.
- Yes. Thank you.

86
00:05:32,570 --> 00:05:34,210
What are you going to do
if your wife finds out?

87
00:05:34,940 --> 00:05:38,510
Come on, it's me.
You think I can't handle my wife?

88
00:05:38,580 --> 00:05:39,880
That's right. You can't.

89
00:05:40,910 --> 00:05:42,250
I agree.

90
00:05:42,880 --> 00:05:46,020
But what's done is done.
How can I undo it?

91
00:05:46,150 --> 00:05:49,490
It's not done. You can undo it.
Give it here.

92
00:05:50,890 --> 00:05:52,860
All we have to do
is not turn this in, right?

93
00:05:54,930 --> 00:05:56,890
So I should just do nothing?

94
00:05:57,100 --> 00:05:58,960
What about the folks
who have been here for decades?

95
00:05:59,030 --> 00:06:01,370
You want me to let them be evicted,
so our Onjeong Market...

96
00:06:01,430 --> 00:06:03,570
can be used to help
Bucket's political career...

97
00:06:03,570 --> 00:06:05,900
when I know his disgusting plan?

98
00:06:06,000 --> 00:06:08,340
- You'd just let that happen?
- Of course not.

99
00:06:08,970 --> 00:06:11,280
But the vote is next week.
Are you sure you can win?

100
00:06:11,340 --> 00:06:12,440
Of course, I am.

101
00:06:12,810 --> 00:06:15,410
I'm the most popular guy
in Onjeong Market.

102
00:06:17,250 --> 00:06:18,420
Right?

103
00:06:18,750 --> 00:06:20,750
Everyone here loves my brother.

104
00:06:21,120 --> 00:06:22,220
All right!

105
00:06:26,160 --> 00:06:29,690
You're unpopular at the market.
You're going to lose, aren't you?

106
00:06:29,990 --> 00:06:33,030
I don't get how they knew to raid us
at that exact moment.

107
00:06:33,500 --> 00:06:36,170
It's a bit of a surprise, I admit,
but don't worry too much.

108
00:06:36,400 --> 00:06:40,610
How can we not worry, Se Ri?
Will anyone even vote for him?

109
00:06:40,670 --> 00:06:42,870
Everyone hates him.

110
00:06:43,140 --> 00:06:46,140
He complains if stalls stick out,
saying they're an eyesore.

111
00:06:46,240 --> 00:06:48,810
He hassles shops with long lines
to clear the area.

112
00:06:49,150 --> 00:06:51,580
He gets rid of bowls for stray cats,
telling people not to feed them.

113
00:06:52,350 --> 00:06:55,350
- Even dogs bark when you walk by.
- Hey!

114
00:06:55,420 --> 00:06:56,690
Dong Suk, please.

115
00:06:57,960 --> 00:07:00,220
Politics isn't about
reading the public's mind.

116
00:07:00,290 --> 00:07:02,030
It's about shaping it.

117
00:07:02,360 --> 00:07:05,500
I'll stack the deck in our favor,
so don't you worry, honey.

118
00:07:06,860 --> 00:07:10,470
Looks like she's dead set
on becoming a councilman's wife.

119
00:07:10,540 --> 00:07:13,570
Dong Suk, my husband
is destined to do great things.

120
00:07:13,640 --> 00:07:14,770
We should aim higher than that.

121
00:07:16,670 --> 00:07:20,950
Honey, this time, I'll ask Father
so we can spend some serious money.

122
00:07:21,580 --> 00:07:25,750
You have a very strange way
of spending money.

123
00:07:25,820 --> 00:07:29,120
You never buy luxury goods.
You just rent them like you're poor.

124
00:07:29,220 --> 00:07:31,890
What's the point?
Trends go out of style so fast.

125
00:07:31,960 --> 00:07:33,690
Renting is
a much more rational choice.

126
00:07:33,890 --> 00:07:37,400
Spending only has value...

127
00:07:37,460 --> 00:07:39,630
when the timing
and the purpose are right, you see.

128
00:07:40,970 --> 00:07:42,170
I see.

129
00:07:42,800 --> 00:07:45,240
Come to think of it,
for the other side to challenge you,

130
00:07:45,500 --> 00:07:47,170
their first worry
will have to be money.

131
00:07:53,780 --> 00:07:55,280
Are you really doing this?

132
00:07:56,180 --> 00:07:57,850
And you! What were you doing?
Why didn't you stop him?

133
00:07:58,150 --> 00:08:00,990
Why do you always take it out on me
when it's his fault?

134
00:08:01,050 --> 00:08:04,290
Come on, Mom. You know this.
To protect the market vendors...

135
00:08:04,360 --> 00:08:05,720
and avoid having to move...

136
00:08:05,720 --> 00:08:08,960
No! How many times must I tell you?
Withdraw your candidacy now.

137
00:08:10,760 --> 00:08:14,570
Cat got your tongue? Not answering?
Still being stubborn, aren't you?

138
00:08:15,230 --> 00:08:18,000
My gosh! Your slaps really sting.
That hurts!

139
00:08:18,600 --> 00:08:21,840
I never thought my sons
would act like this at this age.

140
00:08:21,910 --> 00:08:25,240
You're over 50.
How could you still be so immature?

141
00:08:25,580 --> 00:08:28,350
When will you stop making me nag?

142
00:08:28,410 --> 00:08:31,680
Okay, Mom.
I'll stop him, so please stop.

143
00:08:31,750 --> 00:08:35,020
You'll collapse at this rate.
Calm down. Hey!

144
00:08:35,120 --> 00:08:37,320
- You need to go see your patients.
- I know. Don't touch me.

145
00:08:37,320 --> 00:08:38,960
Your patients are waiting.
Go on. Get going.

146
00:08:40,060 --> 00:08:42,860
- Come on, go! Go already!
- But...

147
00:08:42,860 --> 00:08:45,560
- Mom, I have so much support...
- Goodness. Go, just go.

148
00:08:45,630 --> 00:08:47,300
- But Mom, this...
- Stop, that's enough.

149
00:08:48,930 --> 00:08:50,430
Honestly...

150
00:08:51,940 --> 00:08:53,340
This is just ridiculous.

151
00:08:56,240 --> 00:08:57,240
(Global Strategy Proposal)

152
00:09:02,750 --> 00:09:03,750
What are you up to?

153
00:09:04,420 --> 00:09:06,450
I don't even know anymore.

154
00:09:06,780 --> 00:09:09,320
There's no rhyme or reason
to the tasks he gives me. None.

155
00:09:09,720 --> 00:09:12,960
Hey, it sounds less like a job
and more like a punishment.

156
00:09:13,120 --> 00:09:17,730
Don't tell me they expect me to be
the director's permanent secretary.

157
00:09:18,500 --> 00:09:21,500
No way. I'm sure it's just
to help him out for the time being.

158
00:09:24,340 --> 00:09:26,570
Hey, you guys!

159
00:09:27,270 --> 00:09:30,510
The new director!
I heard he's the VP's boyfriend.

160
00:09:30,880 --> 00:09:34,810
The VP is an only child.
He'll marry her to take over.

161
00:09:35,150 --> 00:09:38,320
- Wow! Are you serious?
- It's straight from an executive.

162
00:09:38,550 --> 00:09:39,980
Hey, where did you hear that?
Who told you?

163
00:09:40,080 --> 00:09:42,990
So Hye, don't go starting
baseless rumors again.

164
00:09:43,120 --> 00:09:45,360
What?
I'm just repeating what I heard.

165
00:09:51,400 --> 00:09:54,900
Hey. What am I going to do?
I went to the VP...

166
00:09:55,300 --> 00:09:57,740
and told her the director
was a stalker and a pervert.

167
00:09:59,340 --> 00:10:02,210
It's just one thing after another.
What are you going to do now?

168
00:10:03,370 --> 00:10:04,980
I should've just quit.

169
00:10:05,640 --> 00:10:07,210
I never should have come back.

170
00:10:13,880 --> 00:10:15,950
Last Saturday's
live home shopping broadcast.

171
00:10:16,250 --> 00:10:18,420
Everyone who went in and out
of the studio that day,

172
00:10:18,420 --> 00:10:21,590
or visited in the days before.
Check every single one.

173
00:10:21,960 --> 00:10:22,960
Understood.

174
00:10:32,740 --> 00:10:35,440
Do you really think someone tampered
with the outfit on purpose?

175
00:10:36,340 --> 00:10:40,240
Maybe not, but we have to make sure.

176
00:10:40,810 --> 00:10:42,680
An innocent person was put
in an awkward position,

177
00:10:42,980 --> 00:10:45,150
and Gong Ju Ah's entire team
got fired.

178
00:10:46,080 --> 00:10:47,180
How can we just let it slide?

179
00:10:48,120 --> 00:10:49,150
Pacu Nacho.

180
00:10:49,550 --> 00:10:51,260
Seriously, what's the deal
between you and Gong Ju Ah?

181
00:10:52,090 --> 00:10:53,720
Can you just drop it, please?

182
00:10:53,920 --> 00:10:57,230
Talk, or I'll tell everybody
that Pacu Nacho is my boyfriend,

183
00:10:57,290 --> 00:11:00,160
and he's marrying me to take over
the company. How about that?

184
00:11:00,230 --> 00:11:01,870
You've already done that.

185
00:11:01,870 --> 00:11:03,800
Everyone was glaring at me
at the executive meeting.

186
00:11:05,040 --> 00:11:06,800
So just spit it out already.

187
00:11:07,270 --> 00:11:09,270
Before I start making up
even more rumors.

188
00:11:14,410 --> 00:11:15,410
She was my first love.

189
00:11:15,650 --> 00:11:17,950
No way! When?

190
00:11:18,320 --> 00:11:19,850
Before you left? How old were you?

191
00:11:19,850 --> 00:11:21,890
I was in 9th grade,
and she was in 10th.

192
00:11:22,890 --> 00:11:23,890
So cute.

193
00:11:25,990 --> 00:11:27,590
Does she even recognize you?

194
00:11:28,260 --> 00:11:31,400
She didn't seem to. She called me
a pervert and a stalker.

195
00:11:32,930 --> 00:11:34,230
This is getting interesting.

196
00:11:35,970 --> 00:11:38,200
This is just the drama
my boring work life needed.

197
00:11:40,300 --> 00:11:41,340
Whatever.

198
00:11:48,510 --> 00:11:52,920
It's past 7 p.m. Where is he?
He's such a slacker, I swear.

199
00:11:58,390 --> 00:11:59,460
Woo Jae? What's up?

200
00:12:01,030 --> 00:12:04,430
When am I getting off?
I have no idea. Why?

201
00:12:06,560 --> 00:12:07,570
What?

202
00:12:08,400 --> 00:12:11,370
Dad's running for president
of the Merchants' Association?

203
00:12:11,770 --> 00:12:13,770
You have got to be kidding me.

204
00:12:14,510 --> 00:12:16,140
Hey, Woo Jae, what about Mom?
Does she know?

205
00:12:17,480 --> 00:12:21,550
No? Good. Make absolutely sure
she doesn't find out. Okay?

206
00:12:23,280 --> 00:12:27,250
Here's the draft of the contract.
Review it and give me your feedback.

207
00:12:27,890 --> 00:12:30,350
This feels suspiciously rushed.

208
00:12:30,890 --> 00:12:33,920
Why do I get the feeling you just
swapped the name on the contract?

209
00:12:34,560 --> 00:12:36,660
Man, you don't miss a thing.

210
00:12:37,630 --> 00:12:38,700
I knew it.

211
00:12:39,060 --> 00:12:41,430
It was originally supposed to be
for Choi Seo Jin.

212
00:12:41,870 --> 00:12:43,670
So why the switch to me?

213
00:12:44,030 --> 00:12:47,040
- What happened with her?
- She's got some serious issues.

214
00:12:48,540 --> 00:12:52,210
Her husband apparently
took investments under her name...

215
00:12:52,740 --> 00:12:53,880
and gambled it all away.

216
00:12:55,450 --> 00:12:58,220
- Oh, my.
- We're killing the stories for now,

217
00:12:58,920 --> 00:13:00,620
but it's only a matter of time
before the story breaks.

218
00:13:01,290 --> 00:13:03,220
That must be a huge blow
to her image.

219
00:13:03,550 --> 00:13:05,220
That's just how
the industry is these days.

220
00:13:05,660 --> 00:13:07,060
It's not just the talent.

221
00:13:07,060 --> 00:13:09,060
Their families
get dragged into it too,

222
00:13:09,290 --> 00:13:12,400
and if one little thing goes wrong,
it's a total media frenzy.

223
00:13:16,370 --> 00:13:17,370
Hold on.

224
00:13:19,100 --> 00:13:21,070
Hui Gyeong? What's going on?

225
00:13:23,140 --> 00:13:24,140
What?

226
00:13:28,010 --> 00:13:29,610
Are we sure about this?

227
00:13:30,410 --> 00:13:35,190
Honey, I think a husband and wife
should never keep secrets.

228
00:13:35,990 --> 00:13:36,990
Right.

229
00:13:37,490 --> 00:13:39,360
We did the right thing
for my brother and his wife, right?

230
00:13:39,420 --> 00:13:42,860
Of course. If you'd kept it a secret
and she found out later,

231
00:13:43,130 --> 00:13:46,900
- you'd have taken the blame for it.
- Yes. You're right.

232
00:13:47,160 --> 00:13:48,170
We did the right thing.

233
00:13:57,110 --> 00:13:59,410
- Hey, Mom.
- I already told you no.

234
00:14:00,180 --> 00:14:02,180
Do you really want Seong Mi
to divorce you?

235
00:14:02,450 --> 00:14:04,550
Come on, I can just
keep it a secret from her.

236
00:14:04,780 --> 00:14:05,780
What did you say?

237
00:14:06,680 --> 00:14:08,720
Okay, fine! I get it.
Goodness gracious.

238
00:14:11,390 --> 00:14:12,390
Oh, dear.

239
00:14:16,190 --> 00:14:18,000
- What?
- What? What is it?

240
00:14:18,300 --> 00:14:19,300
Is that Seong Mi?

241
00:14:20,830 --> 00:14:21,870
Yes.

242
00:14:23,170 --> 00:14:25,000
Yes, honey.

243
00:14:26,540 --> 00:14:28,840
Yes, okay. Got it.

244
00:14:33,780 --> 00:14:34,780
Who was it?

245
00:14:35,650 --> 00:14:36,810
Who snitched?

246
00:14:37,110 --> 00:14:39,150
- Was it you? You?
- It wasn't me!

247
00:14:39,220 --> 00:14:40,220
It wasn't me, either.

248
00:14:42,150 --> 00:14:45,360
- Was it you, Mom?
- Why? What did Seong Mi say?

249
00:14:45,560 --> 00:14:47,930
She said she's on her way
to the clinic right now!

250
00:14:49,190 --> 00:14:50,890
You'd better get going now. Hurry.

251
00:14:52,130 --> 00:14:53,700
Dad, you're so dead.

252
00:14:53,960 --> 00:14:56,300
How could... Mom, this is on you!

253
00:14:57,030 --> 00:14:58,700
Man... I...

254
00:15:02,870 --> 00:15:05,240
I told you to just let them
raise their rent, didn't I?

255
00:15:05,740 --> 00:15:08,680
I told you to stop worrying
about the market.

256
00:15:09,480 --> 00:15:11,320
Seong Mi, please just hear me out.

257
00:15:11,580 --> 00:15:14,080
What?
Merchants' Association President?

258
00:15:14,750 --> 00:15:18,790
- It's a fight for our livelihood...
- Don't make me laugh!

259
00:15:19,560 --> 00:15:23,060
You have a savior complex.

260
00:15:23,490 --> 00:15:27,060
You get your sense of self-worth
from solving others' problems.

261
00:15:27,130 --> 00:15:28,670
It's a narcissistic compulsion.

262
00:15:29,100 --> 00:15:31,970
Okay, fine. I get it, but...

263
00:15:32,900 --> 00:15:37,640
Please, just this once, okay?
Just let me do it my way. Please?

264
00:15:38,040 --> 00:15:40,710
- It won't even cost much money.
- Do you think this is about money?

265
00:15:40,780 --> 00:15:44,620
- Then what is it about?
- Director Song brought my contract.

266
00:15:45,120 --> 00:15:46,680
Do you have any idea what it says?

267
00:15:47,450 --> 00:15:49,250
If I start a scandal
or leave the show...

268
00:15:49,250 --> 00:15:50,420
due to any fault of my own,

269
00:15:50,850 --> 00:15:52,490
my career will be over,

270
00:15:53,060 --> 00:15:55,430
and I have to pay a penalty
equal to three times my fee.

271
00:15:56,030 --> 00:15:59,560
If you get tangled up in some fight
over this election or whatever,

272
00:15:59,700 --> 00:16:01,630
it's going to affect me, too!

273
00:16:02,170 --> 00:16:05,300
That will never happen.
Okay? I promise.

274
00:16:05,300 --> 00:16:07,440
When have you ever kept a promise?

275
00:16:12,210 --> 00:16:13,410
So you really
don't want me to do it?

276
00:16:21,690 --> 00:16:25,360
These are the endorsement letters
I got from the merchants.

277
00:16:25,990 --> 00:16:28,630
If you tell me to stop,
I really won't do it.

278
00:16:28,890 --> 00:16:30,630
I've been trying to stop you
this whole time.

279
00:16:41,510 --> 00:16:42,510
There. Happy?

280
00:16:45,040 --> 00:16:47,680
Honestly, I'm jealous of one thing
when it comes to Yang Dong Ik.

281
00:16:50,650 --> 00:16:53,020
His wife always takes his side,

282
00:16:53,320 --> 00:16:56,790
and she's so supportive,
so he can always hold his head high.

283
00:16:56,890 --> 00:16:58,160
I'm honestly jealous of that.

284
00:17:00,060 --> 00:17:01,090
Are you...

285
00:17:02,760 --> 00:17:04,160
Are you comparing me to her
right now?

286
00:17:05,200 --> 00:17:08,400
- What?
- If she's great, go live with her!

287
00:17:10,630 --> 00:17:11,670
No, that's not what I meant.

288
00:17:12,900 --> 00:17:16,710
My gosh, I shouldn't have said that.
What was I thinking? Oh, boy...

289
00:17:16,770 --> 00:17:18,440
What am I going to do? Man...

290
00:17:24,920 --> 00:17:26,120
(Gong Myeong Jeong Dae Han Clinic)

291
00:17:26,180 --> 00:17:27,180
You scared me.

292
00:17:28,450 --> 00:17:29,490
Hello.

293
00:17:30,550 --> 00:17:31,660
What are you doing here?

294
00:17:31,720 --> 00:17:34,630
Oh, I was just heading home
after a meeting with the PR agency,

295
00:17:34,990 --> 00:17:36,930
but I heard shouting
coming from inside.

296
00:17:37,690 --> 00:17:40,930
- So you were eavesdropping?
- Eavesdropping? No.

297
00:17:41,500 --> 00:17:44,000
Don't worry.
I couldn't hear everything clearly.

298
00:17:44,270 --> 00:17:45,400
Like you didn't hear everything.

299
00:17:47,300 --> 00:17:50,510
I might've heard the part
about you being jealous of me.

300
00:17:50,670 --> 00:17:52,880
Just a little? A tiny bit?

301
00:17:54,450 --> 00:17:57,010
Well, it's a good thing
you stopped him.

302
00:17:57,280 --> 00:18:00,850
Dr. Gong as Merchants' President?
Especially when you're struggling.

303
00:18:01,420 --> 00:18:02,890
Who said we're struggling?

304
00:18:03,220 --> 00:18:07,360
So, I'll just assume
he's dropping out of the race.

305
00:18:07,720 --> 00:18:10,690
You are certainly the wise one.

306
00:18:11,090 --> 00:18:14,030
No point fighting a losing battle,
right?

307
00:18:14,570 --> 00:18:16,170
A losing battle?

308
00:18:17,000 --> 00:18:18,000
See you around.

309
00:18:19,100 --> 00:18:21,840
(Gong Myeong Jeong Dae Han Clinic)

310
00:18:33,550 --> 00:18:35,320
What is it? What's wrong?

311
00:18:36,720 --> 00:18:38,420
Oh, I'm going to throw this out.

312
00:18:38,420 --> 00:18:40,490
I wasn't trying to glue them back
together. I'm throwing these away.

313
00:18:40,560 --> 00:18:41,560
Honey.

314
00:18:42,760 --> 00:18:43,890
Are you really confident?

315
00:18:44,260 --> 00:18:45,260
What?

316
00:18:47,060 --> 00:18:50,600
Yes! I'm confident.
I'll make sure it won't affect you.

317
00:18:50,600 --> 00:18:53,000
Not that.
Are you confident you can win?

318
00:18:53,770 --> 00:18:56,010
I am. Of course, I am!

319
00:18:56,840 --> 00:19:00,340
Don't you dare lose.
You have to win. Got it?

320
00:19:01,150 --> 00:19:02,580
Yes! Got it!

321
00:19:03,550 --> 00:19:05,420
- Seong Mi, thank you.
- My gosh.

322
00:19:06,120 --> 00:19:08,590
- Go away.
- Okay, I'll leave you alone.

323
00:19:09,120 --> 00:19:10,350
But really, thank you.

324
00:19:10,990 --> 00:19:12,360
Yes!

325
00:19:14,490 --> 00:19:16,130
You really let him do it?

326
00:19:16,730 --> 00:19:19,900
I thought you'd be against it.
What made you change your mind?

327
00:19:21,300 --> 00:19:23,600
Just look how happy it makes him.

328
00:19:25,270 --> 00:19:26,540
Thank you so much, Seong Mi.

329
00:19:27,970 --> 00:19:31,580
Mom, I checked the campaign budget,
and it really won't cost much.

330
00:19:32,110 --> 00:19:33,210
That's a relief.

331
00:19:33,280 --> 00:19:35,110
I thought of a few more items
and added them,

332
00:19:35,380 --> 00:19:37,480
and it looks like we'll have to make
the promo materials ourselves.

333
00:19:38,020 --> 00:19:41,820
- I can help with that.
- Thanks, sweetie. Really?

334
00:19:42,420 --> 00:19:46,420
Right. Where do we even start?
Posters? No, the campaign promises?

335
00:19:46,690 --> 00:19:48,590
Yes. Let's do the promises first.
Right?

336
00:19:49,830 --> 00:19:51,500
Oh, man. I'm so nervous!

337
00:19:52,660 --> 00:19:54,330
Dad, calm down.

338
00:19:55,200 --> 00:19:58,240
I can't help it. I'm just so happy.

339
00:20:00,300 --> 00:20:03,240
Pledges... What should I do first?
Any good ideas?

340
00:20:03,310 --> 00:20:05,280
- Just come up with five.
- Five of them?

341
00:20:05,340 --> 00:20:07,380
- Five should be enough.
- Well...

342
00:20:07,440 --> 00:20:09,450
(Taehan)

343
00:20:13,850 --> 00:20:14,850
Oh, boy.

344
00:20:15,720 --> 00:20:17,290
You're here already, sir.

345
00:20:17,490 --> 00:20:21,490
From now on, stop by Latte Monde
and get me a Choco Chip Frappuccino.

346
00:20:23,030 --> 00:20:24,030
Sure.

347
00:20:24,160 --> 00:20:27,460
With low-fat milk, 1 mocha syrup,
and 1 espresso shot.

348
00:20:28,470 --> 00:20:31,440
Add an espresso shot...
Yes, I'll go get it now.

349
00:20:31,500 --> 00:20:33,840
Blend half the chips.
For the topping, use the rest,

350
00:20:33,840 --> 00:20:36,210
with extra whip.
Add a drizzle of chocolate syrup.

351
00:20:38,010 --> 00:20:39,140
Yes, sir.

352
00:20:44,750 --> 00:20:47,580
Set up a snack station.
I need it for brainpower and sugar.

353
00:20:47,950 --> 00:20:48,950
Yes, sir.

354
00:20:48,950 --> 00:20:51,920
Every Monday, list restaurants
for lunch that week.

355
00:20:52,190 --> 00:20:55,330
Korean, Chinese, Japanese,
and Western. Ensure a balanced mix.

356
00:20:55,390 --> 00:20:57,190
They must have
a rating of 4.5 or higher.

357
00:20:58,000 --> 00:20:59,360
Yes, sir.

358
00:21:00,200 --> 00:21:02,300
Air out the office
three times a day.

359
00:21:02,300 --> 00:21:03,330
For the diffuser...

360
00:21:05,870 --> 00:21:07,340
Use a eucalyptus-based scent.

361
00:21:08,210 --> 00:21:09,210
Yes, sir.

362
00:21:11,580 --> 00:21:12,580
And...

363
00:21:13,010 --> 00:21:15,750
Dust everything
to keep the air clean.

364
00:21:16,050 --> 00:21:17,810
- Yes, sir.
- Right away!

365
00:21:18,080 --> 00:21:19,120
Yes, sir!

366
00:21:37,430 --> 00:21:38,800
Bring me the work
I assigned you yesterday.

367
00:21:39,340 --> 00:21:40,500
Yes, sir.

368
00:21:41,640 --> 00:21:43,340
Here are the documents
you requested.

369
00:21:46,740 --> 00:21:50,880
The title font has no impact.
Change it to Gaeseong Art, size 36.

370
00:21:51,420 --> 00:21:52,420
Do it over.

371
00:21:53,480 --> 00:21:54,890
Yes, sir.

372
00:21:55,420 --> 00:21:56,490
(Taehan Group Design Team,
Data Summary)

373
00:22:00,490 --> 00:22:03,190
This is hard to read.
Widen spacing, underline for stress.

374
00:22:03,260 --> 00:22:05,500
Also, it feels more balanced
when the page count is even.

375
00:22:06,500 --> 00:22:08,430
- Do it over.
- Yes, sir.

376
00:22:11,570 --> 00:22:12,640
(Taehan Group Design Team,
Data Summary)

377
00:22:20,510 --> 00:22:22,810
Always staple these diagonally.

378
00:22:22,880 --> 00:22:24,950
Otherwise, the angle is all wrong
when you turn the page!

379
00:22:25,020 --> 00:22:26,520
Do it over!

380
00:22:27,120 --> 00:22:28,120
Yes, sir.

381
00:22:35,030 --> 00:22:36,560
It was just a dream.

382
00:22:51,240 --> 00:22:52,280
Done.

383
00:22:58,080 --> 00:22:59,520
Good morning, sir.

384
00:23:00,650 --> 00:23:03,720
- You're here already?
- Yes. I cleaned and aired it out.

385
00:23:03,790 --> 00:23:06,090
I also stocked the snack station
and set up the diffuser.

386
00:23:10,290 --> 00:23:12,360
From now on,
you don't have to clean my desk.

387
00:23:13,200 --> 00:23:15,600
- I'm sorry?
- I should clean my own desk.

388
00:23:15,970 --> 00:23:17,200
Oh, okay.

389
00:23:17,500 --> 00:23:20,470
What coffee can I get you?
A Chocolate Chip Frappuccino?

390
00:23:21,300 --> 00:23:22,910
I should make my own coffee, too.

391
00:23:25,140 --> 00:23:28,210
Do you need any supplies, then?

392
00:23:28,810 --> 00:23:31,520
I already put in a request
with Support for what I need.

393
00:23:32,680 --> 00:23:33,680
I see.

394
00:23:34,820 --> 00:23:35,820
What's this?

395
00:23:35,890 --> 00:23:38,520
Here are the files you asked for.
They're in reverse date order,

396
00:23:38,520 --> 00:23:40,160
so you can start
with the most recent ones.

397
00:23:41,260 --> 00:23:44,930
You did all this in one day?
You must have stayed late.

398
00:23:45,000 --> 00:23:46,130
Yes, well...

399
00:23:48,730 --> 00:23:50,630
Sorry, I didn't call you yesterday.

400
00:23:50,630 --> 00:23:52,340
I went apartment hunting
after the executive meeting.

401
00:23:52,770 --> 00:23:56,740
Tell me what you're looking for.
I can look into it for you, sir.

402
00:23:57,410 --> 00:24:00,040
Why? That's my personal business.

403
00:24:02,510 --> 00:24:03,510
Right.

404
00:24:40,020 --> 00:24:41,250
Sir...

405
00:24:41,920 --> 00:24:43,620
It's already been three hours.

406
00:24:45,820 --> 00:24:47,090
Has it been that long already?

407
00:24:47,920 --> 00:24:51,030
- Well, should we go get some lunch?
- Sure.

408
00:24:51,460 --> 00:24:54,200
Gyeongmun's has good soft tofu stew,
and so is the pot rice at Cheonghae.

409
00:24:54,260 --> 00:24:58,840
Suwonjang has great jjamppong.
Laura's Grill has good Western food.

410
00:24:58,970 --> 00:25:00,300
What about pork cutlet?

411
00:25:00,800 --> 00:25:02,640
Pork cutlet is my favorite.

412
00:25:03,110 --> 00:25:04,270
Pork cutlet?

413
00:25:06,880 --> 00:25:09,710
There's a place nearby.
Should we go?

414
00:25:11,750 --> 00:25:12,750
Never mind.

415
00:25:13,650 --> 00:25:15,850
Checking out restaurants
is a personal hobby of mine.

416
00:25:15,850 --> 00:25:17,120
Let's not mix business
with pleasure.

417
00:25:17,790 --> 00:25:18,790
What?

418
00:25:32,440 --> 00:25:35,710
Seriously?
You just sat there for three hours?

419
00:25:36,070 --> 00:25:37,240
I know, right?

420
00:25:37,710 --> 00:25:41,040
I was totally prepared
for him to get his revenge.

421
00:25:41,340 --> 00:25:42,810
But he's not giving me a hard time
at all.

422
00:25:43,180 --> 00:25:47,020
Clever. He knew you'd be prepared,
so he held back?

423
00:25:47,080 --> 00:25:50,820
That's what I'm saying.
He's as unpredictable as ever.

424
00:25:51,450 --> 00:25:53,960
- I'll have to be extra careful.
- Hello.

425
00:25:55,430 --> 00:25:59,030
- Do you mind if I sit here?
- Not at all. Please, have a seat.

426
00:26:07,770 --> 00:26:08,770
There we go.

427
00:26:11,940 --> 00:26:14,010
- Enjoy your meal.
- You, too.

428
00:26:16,280 --> 00:26:18,080
- What?
- Just eat.

429
00:26:29,030 --> 00:26:31,330
The food in our cafeteria
is incredible.

430
00:26:31,960 --> 00:26:36,870
I thought lotus root would be chewy,
but it's wonderfully crisp.

431
00:26:36,930 --> 00:26:40,800
And you get that hint of ginger.
Truly the work of a master chef.

432
00:26:45,780 --> 00:26:48,850
But isn't a one-hour lunch break...

433
00:26:48,910 --> 00:26:50,410
a little stingy, Seong Min?

434
00:26:50,910 --> 00:26:51,950
Pardon?

435
00:26:53,120 --> 00:26:54,450
Me?

436
00:26:56,020 --> 00:26:59,220
Shouldn't you have time to eat,
take a little walk,

437
00:26:59,290 --> 00:27:01,930
grab some coffee,
and chat for a bit, too?

438
00:27:02,230 --> 00:27:05,230
That's how you come back refreshed
and work more efficiently.

439
00:27:05,700 --> 00:27:07,460
- Right, So Hye?
- Pardon?

440
00:27:08,160 --> 00:27:09,170
Right.

441
00:27:12,270 --> 00:27:13,270
Go on, eat.

442
00:27:16,070 --> 00:27:17,070
Just eat.

443
00:27:31,720 --> 00:27:34,990
- He knows everyone's name already.
- I know, right?

444
00:27:35,490 --> 00:27:37,890
He only heard them this morning.
When did he have time to learn them?

445
00:27:38,830 --> 00:27:42,030
What do you think he's trying to do,
winning everyone over?

446
00:27:43,330 --> 00:27:47,940
Maybe he just wants to get along.
He doesn't seem to hold a grudge.

447
00:27:49,210 --> 00:27:51,040
I can't let my guard down
for one second.

448
00:28:13,500 --> 00:28:14,560
(Mock Medical Licensing Exam)

449
00:28:32,180 --> 00:28:33,180
Woo Jae.

450
00:28:33,580 --> 00:28:34,580
(Trazodone)

451
00:28:35,490 --> 00:28:37,820
- What meds are you taking?
- Why are you here?

452
00:28:37,890 --> 00:28:39,490
I came to see you, silly.

453
00:28:42,560 --> 00:28:44,990
Seriously, what's wrong?
Why are you taking medicine?

454
00:28:44,990 --> 00:28:46,560
It's just for a headache.

455
00:28:46,660 --> 00:28:49,870
Seriously! How dare you get sick
without my permission?

456
00:28:49,870 --> 00:28:51,870
If you keep showing up,
I'm switching study cafes.

457
00:28:51,940 --> 00:28:55,410
It's no use. I'd find you
no matter where you hid.

458
00:28:56,870 --> 00:29:00,140
Eun Bin, don't you have any dreams?

459
00:29:00,210 --> 00:29:03,180
Try something with a future.
Or get a hobby, at least.

460
00:29:03,250 --> 00:29:06,420
Hey, I'm an influencer, you know.

461
00:29:06,480 --> 00:29:08,890
You can't be an influencer
with 250 followers.

462
00:29:08,950 --> 00:29:10,790
Hey, that's a lot of followers!

463
00:29:10,790 --> 00:29:13,290
Just you wait.
I'll get the Pink Button.

464
00:29:14,790 --> 00:29:17,630
Right. Good for you.
It's good to be positive.

465
00:29:18,600 --> 00:29:20,000
What? Hey!

466
00:29:21,460 --> 00:29:24,630
I heard Father is running for
Merchants' Association president.

467
00:29:25,140 --> 00:29:27,600
"Father?"
Are you talking about my dad?

468
00:29:27,770 --> 00:29:31,840
Gosh, I'm so torn.
Who do I root for?

469
00:29:32,040 --> 00:29:35,750
My dad or yours?
That is the question.

470
00:29:35,980 --> 00:29:37,510
Root for your own dad.

471
00:29:39,220 --> 00:29:41,580
Hey, do you want me to be your spy?

472
00:29:42,320 --> 00:29:45,390
- What?
- Like the movies, risking it all.

473
00:29:45,460 --> 00:29:48,260
I'll leak my dad's campaign strategy
to you.

474
00:29:50,130 --> 00:29:51,900
So what's the strategy?

475
00:29:52,600 --> 00:29:55,600
If I tell you,
we'll start dating today. Deal?

476
00:29:58,370 --> 00:30:02,270
Come on, there's no free lunch!
Ever heard of give and take?

477
00:30:02,270 --> 00:30:03,270
And you call yourself educated?

478
00:30:05,740 --> 00:30:10,210
Great pose. Okay, let's try another.
Good. Yes, your right hand. Great.

479
00:30:10,910 --> 00:30:13,450
Great. Okay, I'm taking the picture.
One, two, three! That's great.

480
00:30:13,450 --> 00:30:14,450
That's it. So handsome.

481
00:30:14,520 --> 00:30:16,450
Yes, cross your arms for me.
Perfect. Fantastic. That's great.

482
00:30:18,020 --> 00:30:19,990
- Have some water, honey.
- Okay.

483
00:30:20,820 --> 00:30:22,830
With you here,
I feel like I can do anything.

484
00:30:23,460 --> 00:30:25,030
So handsome.

485
00:30:25,300 --> 00:30:26,300
My goodness.

486
00:30:27,160 --> 00:30:31,900
Now a smile, with a determined pose!
Great. Yes, that's it.

487
00:30:32,000 --> 00:30:35,610
Yes, that's it. Fire in your eyes.
One, two, three! Look at the camera!

488
00:30:44,250 --> 00:30:45,450
He's just amazing.

489
00:30:51,350 --> 00:30:53,920
A simple headshot was all we needed.

490
00:30:53,920 --> 00:30:56,030
He's not running
for the National Assembly.

491
00:30:56,030 --> 00:30:59,460
So why spend all this money
on a Merchants' Association vote?

492
00:30:59,460 --> 00:31:02,000
If we're going to do it,
we should do it right.

493
00:31:02,830 --> 00:31:04,970
Dong Ik, did you see the budget
from the PR firm?

494
00:31:05,400 --> 00:31:08,340
What's all this about merchandise?
And hiring a singer? It's too much.

495
00:31:08,540 --> 00:31:10,740
Why did you tag along
just to nitpick everything I do?

496
00:31:13,680 --> 00:31:15,250
I wonder
what the other side is up to.

497
00:31:16,450 --> 00:31:18,480
Well, what could they
possibly be doing?

498
00:31:19,550 --> 00:31:20,920
- Nice!
- Oh, come on in.

499
00:31:20,980 --> 00:31:22,390
That's it, great expression.

500
00:31:22,720 --> 00:31:24,020
- Yes, it's a pleasure.
- This is so great!

501
00:31:24,090 --> 00:31:26,620
- Nice!
- Hey, that's so you. Smile!

502
00:31:26,690 --> 00:31:28,490
- Okay.
- Bow.

503
00:31:28,490 --> 00:31:29,990
You're always welcome!
Yes. Goodness.

504
00:31:30,030 --> 00:31:32,700
That's it! Applause!
Again, greet them.

505
00:31:33,330 --> 00:31:34,330
Look at Mr. Shin.

506
00:31:34,430 --> 00:31:36,630
Oh, my.
You're looking so much better.

507
00:31:36,630 --> 00:31:38,300
- Shake his hand!
- Right, a handshake.

508
00:31:38,370 --> 00:31:39,770
- With warmth!
- Oh, my.

509
00:31:39,840 --> 00:31:41,770
- Yes, get a tight shot.
- You'll feel better in no time.

510
00:31:41,840 --> 00:31:44,910
Could you get a little closer?
Yes, great.

511
00:31:45,010 --> 00:31:48,240
All right, that's great.
Give us a smile. One, two, three!

512
00:31:48,710 --> 00:31:51,710
- Say "Cheese!" One, two, three!
- Cheese!

513
00:31:51,780 --> 00:31:52,820
That's great.

514
00:31:53,680 --> 00:31:55,590
- This one! Hey!
- This one?

515
00:31:55,650 --> 00:31:56,650
This one's great. I like it.

516
00:31:56,720 --> 00:32:00,520
Yes, this one's got a great feel.
The sign shop will give us a deal.

517
00:32:00,520 --> 00:32:01,520
I'll place the order right away.

518
00:32:01,590 --> 00:32:04,030
Send that to Ju Ah, too.
She said she'd make the flyers.

519
00:32:04,330 --> 00:32:05,330
Okay.

520
00:32:05,600 --> 00:32:07,130
- Let me see.
- Is this really going to be enough?

521
00:32:07,600 --> 00:32:09,470
I heard the other side
hired professionals for everything.

522
00:32:09,600 --> 00:32:12,440
Please. It's just for
the Merchants' Association election.

523
00:32:12,600 --> 00:32:15,170
Sincerity is what counts.

524
00:32:15,270 --> 00:32:17,970
You're right. Defeating Bucket
will be a piece of cake.

525
00:32:18,510 --> 00:32:20,980
- It turned out great.
- Give it to me. I'll go order it.

526
00:32:21,780 --> 00:32:22,780
(Candidate 1 Yang Dong Ik)

527
00:32:24,150 --> 00:32:25,350
(The expert who knows
Onjeong Market best)

528
00:32:28,320 --> 00:32:29,720
I feel like a whole new man.

529
00:32:29,720 --> 00:32:31,420
- It came out great.
- Right?

530
00:32:32,490 --> 00:32:33,690
This is good.

531
00:32:34,590 --> 00:32:37,630
Dae Han. Just like you said,
it came out with a really nice feel.

532
00:32:38,330 --> 00:32:39,430
Looking so handsome!

533
00:32:39,530 --> 00:32:41,800
(Onjeong Traditional Market)

534
00:32:42,300 --> 00:32:43,730
Did you take this with your phone?

535
00:32:44,230 --> 00:32:47,640
How much did you retouch this?
Your laugh lines are all gone.

536
00:32:47,700 --> 00:32:49,410
Retouching is
standard procedure now.

537
00:32:49,610 --> 00:32:52,240
Come on, let's go.
You promised your wife not to fight.

538
00:32:52,310 --> 00:32:54,510
You're right.
I'm not supposed to fight.

539
00:32:56,680 --> 00:32:59,650
(Candidate 1 Yang Dong Ik)

540
00:32:59,820 --> 00:33:01,480
Come on, Mr. Chairman,
let's head in.

541
00:33:12,700 --> 00:33:15,970
Excuse me, sir.
I'm sorry to have to say this,

542
00:33:16,470 --> 00:33:19,270
but we can't have you slacking off
and sunbathing every day.

543
00:33:19,570 --> 00:33:20,670
We just can't.

544
00:33:21,040 --> 00:33:25,580
Come on, I'm not slacking off.
I'm people-watching right now.

545
00:33:26,610 --> 00:33:27,610
Sorry?

546
00:33:29,080 --> 00:33:33,050
Reading reports doesn't help me
understand fashion or design.

547
00:33:33,550 --> 00:33:37,850
I just rebranded a meat company,
so this is a whole new world for me.

548
00:33:39,020 --> 00:33:43,730
So I decided to just observe people.
People-watching.

549
00:33:45,830 --> 00:33:47,400
To see what clothes they're wearing,

550
00:33:47,730 --> 00:33:50,130
and the look on their faces
when they wear them.

551
00:33:52,840 --> 00:33:54,370
Whatever the brand,

552
00:33:54,670 --> 00:33:58,210
ultimately, my job is
to resonate with people.

553
00:34:09,620 --> 00:34:10,950
(In front of elevators)

554
00:34:11,020 --> 00:34:13,590
(West entrance)

555
00:34:13,660 --> 00:34:15,220
(B1 parking lot)

556
00:34:18,090 --> 00:34:20,860
I passed on the CCTV footage
from that day to the new director.

557
00:34:21,160 --> 00:34:22,270
You gave it to the director?

558
00:34:23,000 --> 00:34:24,730
Why would he need that?

559
00:34:26,500 --> 00:34:27,500
Why do you ask?

560
00:34:27,940 --> 00:34:31,510
If we find there's an issue,
it's for the company to handle.

561
00:34:32,740 --> 00:34:34,940
Don't you worry about it, Ms. Gong.
Just focus on your work.

562
00:34:36,380 --> 00:34:38,250
Okay, thank you.

563
00:34:43,890 --> 00:34:46,660
What is with that unpredictable,
thoughtful side of his?

564
00:34:47,260 --> 00:34:49,590
He's more dedicated to his work
than I thought, too.

565
00:34:50,090 --> 00:34:51,090
Ms. Gong?

566
00:34:51,990 --> 00:34:54,700
- Yes, sir?
- I was looking at your portfolio,

567
00:34:54,760 --> 00:34:58,530
and it had a raw sensibility
and a strong experimental vibe.

568
00:34:58,840 --> 00:35:03,440
Your new work's more conventional.
Is there a reason for that?

569
00:35:05,040 --> 00:35:08,950
For big brands, sales come first.
And you have to minimize risk,

570
00:35:09,210 --> 00:35:11,380
so it's hard to inject
my own personal style into it.

571
00:35:11,710 --> 00:35:13,250
You have to follow
the brand's direction.

572
00:35:13,920 --> 00:35:16,190
That makes sense.

573
00:35:22,930 --> 00:35:25,530
My new car was delivered today.
Can I give you a ride home?

574
00:35:26,000 --> 00:35:28,530
Isn't your hotel nearby, sir?

575
00:35:28,700 --> 00:35:31,970
Oh, I'm actually going to visit
my family today.

576
00:35:32,200 --> 00:35:33,970
It's on my way,
so I can just drop you off.

577
00:35:35,000 --> 00:35:38,570
But do you even know where I live?

578
00:35:42,810 --> 00:35:46,620
I saw your HR file.
You live in Onjeong, right?

579
00:35:47,080 --> 00:35:49,020
Yes, that's right. Onjeong.

580
00:35:49,490 --> 00:35:53,290
- So your family lives near Onjeong.
- Yes.

581
00:35:53,790 --> 00:35:55,730
I see.

582
00:36:10,810 --> 00:36:11,870
There we go. Perfect.

583
00:36:17,750 --> 00:36:20,750
- This is delicious.
- How is it? Good?

584
00:36:20,820 --> 00:36:23,220
Yes, it's a feast fit for a king.

585
00:36:23,290 --> 00:36:26,860
- You should cook like this often.
- Tell me about it.

586
00:36:28,120 --> 00:36:30,160
Why are you all sitting around
while Se Ri does everything?

587
00:36:30,490 --> 00:36:32,130
No, that's not it.

588
00:36:32,500 --> 00:36:35,500
We were working this whole time.
We just sat down for a break.

589
00:36:36,570 --> 00:36:40,200
Grandpa, I need to buy
some new filming equipment.

590
00:36:40,270 --> 00:36:41,770
Could you give me some money?

591
00:36:42,810 --> 00:36:44,410
Are you out of your mind?

592
00:36:45,140 --> 00:36:48,140
You've graduated, so get a job.
What's with this "filming?"

593
00:36:49,280 --> 00:36:52,550
Come on, Dad. Go easy on her.
She's your only granddaughter.

594
00:36:52,650 --> 00:36:54,550
Quiet! And that goes for you, too.

595
00:36:56,350 --> 00:36:57,550
You're all a bunch of leeches.

596
00:36:58,020 --> 00:36:59,290
- Grandfather!
- Dad!

597
00:37:00,460 --> 00:37:02,930
Here you go, Father.
I was just about to bring you some.

598
00:37:02,990 --> 00:37:05,460
- Have some while it's hot.
- Give me more.

599
00:37:05,600 --> 00:37:09,300
Not yet. We're waiting for Hyun Bin.
Just have a taste for now, Father.

600
00:37:09,830 --> 00:37:10,830
Fine.

601
00:37:11,570 --> 00:37:13,840
Auntie, why does Grandfather
hate us so much?

602
00:37:14,100 --> 00:37:17,410
Hey! Do you really have to ask?
You take after your mother who left,

603
00:37:17,510 --> 00:37:20,880
and I take after my mother who left.
That's why he can't stand us.

604
00:37:21,210 --> 00:37:23,450
It's so frustrating.
He only ever dotes on my stepmom.

605
00:37:24,210 --> 00:37:25,780
If only you two were
half as good as Se Ri,

606
00:37:26,180 --> 00:37:27,350
I'd spoil you rotten.

607
00:37:27,680 --> 00:37:29,920
Great, Dad's starting
his usual spiel.

608
00:37:30,490 --> 00:37:31,990
She saved me
when I was on my deathbed,

609
00:37:32,090 --> 00:37:35,520
and she's the one who made
our family into what it is today.

610
00:37:43,100 --> 00:37:44,370
What's with Grandpa?

611
00:37:56,880 --> 00:37:59,120
How long has it been since
you last visited your family home?

612
00:37:59,950 --> 00:38:03,920
I believe you said you moved out
when you were a teenager.

613
00:38:04,190 --> 00:38:07,120
Oh, I did move back for a bit
for my military service.

614
00:38:07,620 --> 00:38:08,890
So after I was discharged...

615
00:38:09,630 --> 00:38:10,760
I guess it's been about ten years?

616
00:38:11,030 --> 00:38:12,360
I see.

617
00:38:13,300 --> 00:38:14,760
That must feel a little awkward.

618
00:38:15,770 --> 00:38:18,300
Tell me about it.
I don't really want to go,

619
00:38:18,900 --> 00:38:21,370
but they know I'm back in Korea,
so I have to show my face once.

620
00:38:23,310 --> 00:38:27,010
Maybe because it's been so long,
I'm actually a little nervous.

621
00:38:30,310 --> 00:38:32,450
In that case...

622
00:38:32,950 --> 00:38:36,390
To help you relax,
could I ask you a question?

623
00:38:36,450 --> 00:38:37,450
Sure, anything.

624
00:38:38,250 --> 00:38:41,460
How did you end up
getting into branding?

625
00:38:43,690 --> 00:38:47,560
I've always liked
making obscure things shine.

626
00:38:48,360 --> 00:38:52,770
When I saw unloved brands,
pushed aside and forgotten,

627
00:38:53,640 --> 00:38:55,300
that didn't belong anywhere,

628
00:38:55,840 --> 00:38:58,070
I saw a reflection of myself,
just drifting.

629
00:39:09,320 --> 00:39:11,250
Thank you for the ride.

630
00:39:11,850 --> 00:39:14,420
- Go on in.
- Yes. Drive safe.

631
00:39:37,310 --> 00:39:38,910
This place hasn't changed a bit.

632
00:40:07,940 --> 00:40:08,940
Hey, Yang Hyun Bin.

633
00:40:09,980 --> 00:40:11,410
What are you doing on this street,
you jinx?

634
00:40:11,780 --> 00:40:14,280
You're an embarrassment.
Didn't we tell you to move?

635
00:40:15,050 --> 00:40:16,890
Your grandma had an affair,
and your mom cheated on your dad.

636
00:40:17,090 --> 00:40:18,090
Have you no shame?

637
00:40:18,850 --> 00:40:21,620
Hey, I bet every girl he dates
is going to cheat on him, too.

638
00:40:25,760 --> 00:40:26,760
What was that? Darn...

639
00:40:27,660 --> 00:40:29,700
What do you think? You little...

640
00:40:30,670 --> 00:40:32,130
I'm Gong Ju Ah, his savior.

641
00:40:33,000 --> 00:40:34,070
Whatever.

642
00:40:34,070 --> 00:40:37,540
How dare you punks cause trouble
in our sacred alleys? It's assault!

643
00:40:37,540 --> 00:40:40,380
We didn't assault anyone.
You're the one who hit us.

644
00:40:40,380 --> 00:40:42,850
Hey, verbal assault
is still assault!

645
00:40:43,210 --> 00:40:45,710
You guys started it,
so I was just defending him.

646
00:40:45,780 --> 00:40:47,080
You rotten little punks!

647
00:40:47,750 --> 00:40:52,220
If you ever mess with him again,
I'll tear you limb from limb.

648
00:40:53,020 --> 00:40:56,490
They call me the Hyena of Onjeong.
Why?

649
00:40:57,230 --> 00:41:00,300
Because once I sink my teeth in,
I never let go.

650
00:41:00,900 --> 00:41:01,900
Like this!

651
00:41:03,100 --> 00:41:04,630
What the... Hey, let's go.

652
00:41:11,010 --> 00:41:12,640
Are you okay, Hyun Bin?

653
00:41:13,540 --> 00:41:15,210
Yes, Ju Ah.

654
00:41:17,250 --> 00:41:18,950
It's the adults' fault.

655
00:41:19,550 --> 00:41:20,950
It's not your fault at all.

656
00:41:21,820 --> 00:41:24,390
Okay. Thank you.

657
00:41:25,450 --> 00:41:27,760
What should we eat
to make you feel better?

658
00:41:29,330 --> 00:41:31,060
I heard a great new pork cutlet spot
just opened.

659
00:41:32,190 --> 00:41:33,230
Do you like pork cutlets?

660
00:41:33,860 --> 00:41:34,860
Yes.

661
00:41:35,400 --> 00:41:36,400
I do.

662
00:41:37,930 --> 00:41:38,930
Let's go.

663
00:41:53,280 --> 00:41:54,350
I like you.

664
00:41:55,180 --> 00:41:56,590
It's not the pork cutlets I like.

665
00:41:57,490 --> 00:41:59,890
It's you, Gong Ju Ah.

666
00:42:23,810 --> 00:42:24,810
How have you been?

667
00:42:25,880 --> 00:42:27,050
You still recognize me,
don't you, Grandpa?

668
00:42:27,350 --> 00:42:28,350
You little brat.

669
00:42:28,780 --> 00:42:31,820
Seeing as you recognize me,
you haven't lost your marbles yet.

670
00:42:32,120 --> 00:42:34,460
You look a lot older, though.

671
00:42:34,820 --> 00:42:35,820
What was that?

672
00:42:36,530 --> 00:42:38,530
Looks like all you've learned
is how to be bratty.

673
00:42:39,530 --> 00:42:41,430
Enough wandering around.
Move back home.

674
00:42:42,530 --> 00:42:44,400
No thanks. Not until after
you're gone, Grandpa.

675
00:42:44,800 --> 00:42:45,830
Before I die...

676
00:42:47,340 --> 00:42:50,670
- You little brat!
- Man, I'm hungry.

677
00:42:51,240 --> 00:42:52,980
I'm hungry.
I might as well eat before I go.

678
00:43:16,930 --> 00:43:20,570
If I knew Stepmother cooked so well,
I would've never studied abroad.

679
00:43:21,570 --> 00:43:22,640
Thanks for the compliment.

680
00:43:24,240 --> 00:43:26,680
You're the eldest son
of this family.

681
00:43:27,940 --> 00:43:29,650
No more of this nonsense.

682
00:43:30,380 --> 00:43:32,250
Become a Korean medicine doctor
like your father.

683
00:43:32,880 --> 00:43:35,020
Father,
why are you bringing this up now?

684
00:43:35,420 --> 00:43:36,990
Do you even know
how old Hyun Bin is?

685
00:43:37,990 --> 00:43:41,360
Father, Hyun Bin...
You know the Taehan Group, right?

686
00:43:41,990 --> 00:43:43,230
He's a director
at that huge corporation.

687
00:43:43,590 --> 00:43:44,590
And what about it?

688
00:43:46,230 --> 00:43:47,830
- Water.
- Yes.

689
00:43:51,300 --> 00:43:53,700
I have absolutely no intention of
becoming a Korean medicine doctor.

690
00:43:54,000 --> 00:43:56,040
Nor do I intend
to inherit the clinic.

691
00:43:56,340 --> 00:43:58,240
And I'm not coming back
to this house, so...

692
00:43:58,640 --> 00:44:01,540
Please, stop serving him
and eat something, Stepmother.

693
00:44:02,210 --> 00:44:04,310
Dad, don't you have hands?

694
00:44:04,580 --> 00:44:06,320
Do you think you're a king
from the Joseon era or something?

695
00:44:09,750 --> 00:44:11,020
Just stop. You should eat, too.

696
00:44:11,720 --> 00:44:12,720
I'll take care of myself.

697
00:44:13,820 --> 00:44:16,860
Really, it's okay, Hyun Bin.
I don't mind.

698
00:44:17,190 --> 00:44:19,760
You haven't been here in a while.
Let's eat with a smile, okay?

699
00:44:20,600 --> 00:44:22,060
What do you have to smile about?

700
00:44:22,400 --> 00:44:25,530
Why do you think he stays away?
It's your fault.

701
00:44:25,770 --> 00:44:29,040
I let it go when you were a kid,
but come on.

702
00:44:29,140 --> 00:44:30,770
How can you still be
so disrespectful?

703
00:44:31,210 --> 00:44:33,580
She's raised you
since you were in grade school.

704
00:44:33,840 --> 00:44:34,840
Grow up, Yang Eun Bin.

705
00:44:37,510 --> 00:44:38,510
You.

706
00:44:39,720 --> 00:44:42,790
While you were away, did you stay
with that mother of yours?

707
00:44:43,450 --> 00:44:44,450
Father.

708
00:44:44,990 --> 00:44:46,460
Why are you bringing that woman up?

709
00:44:47,160 --> 00:44:50,190
There's no way the woman who left
her own kids would've contacted him.

710
00:44:50,760 --> 00:44:52,290
I'm the one who reached out to her.
We met.

711
00:44:54,930 --> 00:44:56,330
So that's it.

712
00:44:57,530 --> 00:45:01,200
That's why you're so arrogant.
You think someone has your back.

713
00:45:02,370 --> 00:45:05,970
Did she tell you to ignore us?
Is that why you haven't reached out?

714
00:45:06,480 --> 00:45:10,410
- Seriously, where does she live?
- I don't know.

715
00:45:11,310 --> 00:45:16,150
We only wrote while I was abroad.
I met her once during my service.

716
00:45:16,620 --> 00:45:17,620
What did she say?

717
00:45:18,220 --> 00:45:20,320
What on earth did she say to you?

718
00:45:20,820 --> 00:45:22,460
She told me
never to contact her again.

719
00:45:24,030 --> 00:45:27,360
- What?
- She said I look just like you two,

720
00:45:27,800 --> 00:45:30,400
and that I remind her
of that misery,

721
00:45:30,400 --> 00:45:31,570
so she never wants to see me again.

722
00:45:35,270 --> 00:45:38,340
Did you really have to say that
in front of Grandfather?

723
00:45:38,740 --> 00:45:40,510
Stop making things so hard
on Stepmother.

724
00:45:40,510 --> 00:45:42,010
You don't want another divorce.

725
00:45:42,180 --> 00:45:45,480
- What was that?
- Wrong. My dad and brother...

726
00:45:45,550 --> 00:45:47,150
treat her incredibly well.

727
00:45:47,620 --> 00:45:50,720
She waits on them hand and foot.
Of course, they should.

728
00:45:51,550 --> 00:45:54,760
Wait, why are you taking her side?
If Dad had never remarried,

729
00:45:54,820 --> 00:45:56,430
you wouldn't have had
to go study abroad.

730
00:45:56,490 --> 00:45:59,600
Hey! If he hadn't remarried,
who would have raised you two?

731
00:45:59,660 --> 00:46:00,660
Was I supposed to?

732
00:46:01,160 --> 00:46:04,470
After my mom left,
I did all the housework.

733
00:46:04,570 --> 00:46:07,800
I was the one who had to take care
of my brother and our father.

734
00:46:08,040 --> 00:46:09,370
So? Did you raise my kids?

735
00:46:10,070 --> 00:46:13,010
You ran off and married, didn't you?
She's the one who did the hard work.

736
00:46:13,080 --> 00:46:14,810
Hard work? What did she do?

737
00:46:14,810 --> 00:46:17,050
He studied abroad,
and I grew up on my own!

738
00:46:17,110 --> 00:46:20,320
Come on, everyone, that's enough.
Let's just eat.

739
00:46:20,380 --> 00:46:22,280
It's a special occasion.
Why are you all doing this?

740
00:46:23,120 --> 00:46:25,290
Hyun Bin, go on and eat. Okay?

741
00:46:27,860 --> 00:46:29,660
I was really looking forward
to a home-cooked meal,

742
00:46:30,790 --> 00:46:31,890
but I've completely
lost my appetite.

743
00:46:44,510 --> 00:46:47,010
Right. My phone.
Go wait in the room.

744
00:46:48,910 --> 00:46:53,380
You must study Korean medicine.
You heard what Hyun Bin said, right?

745
00:46:54,680 --> 00:46:56,650
He said
he's not interested in the clinic.

746
00:46:57,250 --> 00:46:58,890
And your uncle wants
to go into politics.

747
00:46:59,220 --> 00:47:03,460
So if you just get into that school,
the clinic will be yours. Got it?

748
00:47:04,590 --> 00:47:08,000
Hey, are you listening to me or not?

749
00:47:08,760 --> 00:47:10,500
So Hyun Bin's really not moving in?

750
00:47:11,370 --> 00:47:12,600
That means we won't get kicked out,
right?

751
00:47:13,000 --> 00:47:16,170
I'll stop him. He hated it here.
He can't just waltz back in.

752
00:47:16,540 --> 00:47:17,540
Exactly.

753
00:47:28,220 --> 00:47:30,490
I wish you would stay
and live with us here in Korea.

754
00:47:31,090 --> 00:47:33,460
I want to be a real mother to you.

755
00:47:34,190 --> 00:47:36,390
You can,
for as long as I'm in Korea.

756
00:47:36,990 --> 00:47:39,560
Really? Then I can help you
find a studio apartment...

757
00:47:39,630 --> 00:47:41,230
and bring you home-cooked meals?

758
00:47:42,900 --> 00:47:44,970
I'll even give you
the passcode to my front door.

759
00:47:45,270 --> 00:47:47,100
Wow, that's so exciting!

760
00:47:48,770 --> 00:47:52,170
Why didn't you ever have
kids of your own?

761
00:47:52,770 --> 00:47:54,310
You would've been a great mom.

762
00:47:57,710 --> 00:48:00,450
So I could pour all my love
into you and Eun Bin.

763
00:48:03,020 --> 00:48:05,550
Dad's a lucky man.

764
00:48:08,190 --> 00:48:12,090
Don't be too hard on your father.
He's just starved for affection.

765
00:48:12,860 --> 00:48:14,200
He wants to be loved by people...

766
00:48:14,560 --> 00:48:17,500
and respected. That's why
he's getting into politics.

767
00:48:17,770 --> 00:48:21,370
- Then he should act respectably.
- I'm going to make sure he does.

768
00:48:21,900 --> 00:48:24,940
I'm going to make him whole.

769
00:48:26,740 --> 00:48:27,740
Thank you.

770
00:48:41,490 --> 00:48:42,620
Did Hyun Bin leave?

771
00:48:43,730 --> 00:48:47,060
If you were happy to see him,
you didn't have to be so harsh.

772
00:48:50,600 --> 00:48:51,630
What's wrong?

773
00:48:52,730 --> 00:48:53,870
Do I...

774
00:48:55,040 --> 00:48:56,240
make your life difficult?

775
00:48:57,410 --> 00:48:59,570
What a thing to say.
That's not like you.

776
00:49:00,910 --> 00:49:02,310
The way I doubt you,

777
00:49:02,840 --> 00:49:04,310
track your location
and everything...

778
00:49:05,510 --> 00:49:06,550
Do you hate me for it?

779
00:49:07,350 --> 00:49:08,680
Hate you? Of course not.

780
00:49:09,120 --> 00:49:11,290
I know exactly why
you do those things.

781
00:49:14,560 --> 00:49:15,590
I...

782
00:49:17,030 --> 00:49:18,730
I'm never, ever going to leave you.

783
00:49:19,430 --> 00:49:22,900
You of all people know
what my life has been like.

784
00:49:23,570 --> 00:49:26,440
I love this house.
And I love you so much.

785
00:49:27,070 --> 00:49:28,970
So don't you worry.

786
00:49:46,490 --> 00:49:48,990
My goodness. What is this?

787
00:49:58,570 --> 00:49:59,900
(Novagen)

788
00:50:02,400 --> 00:50:03,640
Why is this...

789
00:50:07,940 --> 00:50:11,650
Ma'am, come and get some lunch.
We're having gimbap...

790
00:50:14,250 --> 00:50:15,380
Where did she go?

791
00:50:16,150 --> 00:50:17,820
Maybe she went out
campaigning with the others?

792
00:50:19,790 --> 00:50:21,190
Tell me, Hui Gyeong.

793
00:50:21,860 --> 00:50:23,560
Why are you on birth control?

794
00:50:24,490 --> 00:50:26,260
The thing is...

795
00:50:27,100 --> 00:50:28,360
Go on. What is it?

796
00:50:29,430 --> 00:50:31,170
I don't want to have children.

797
00:50:34,770 --> 00:50:36,300
Is this about money?

798
00:50:36,840 --> 00:50:39,240
Are you putting it off
because money is tight?

799
00:50:40,080 --> 00:50:42,640
- If that's the case, I can...
- No, that's not it.

800
00:50:43,650 --> 00:50:44,780
If it's not that, then what is it?

801
00:50:45,480 --> 00:50:46,580
The thing is...

802
00:50:47,580 --> 00:50:50,150
I'm just scared, and I'm not sure
I can raise a child.

803
00:50:53,220 --> 00:50:54,890
How long have you felt this way?

804
00:50:56,830 --> 00:50:58,160
Since before we were married.

805
00:51:00,230 --> 00:51:04,470
Then why didn't you tell Dae Han?
You know how badly he wants kids.

806
00:51:04,870 --> 00:51:07,140
I know.
If I told him I didn't want one,

807
00:51:07,200 --> 00:51:09,100
I was afraid he wouldn't marry me.

808
00:51:12,140 --> 00:51:16,410
Mother, can't you please
just pretend you don't know?

809
00:51:16,850 --> 00:51:19,850
What happens between a couple
is their own business.

810
00:51:20,320 --> 00:51:21,350
Right?

811
00:51:25,590 --> 00:51:27,960
- Thank you.
- We'd appreciate your support.

812
00:51:28,490 --> 00:51:30,630
Hello!
I'm Gong Jeong Han, number two.

813
00:51:30,630 --> 00:51:32,730
- Vote for number 2.
- Number 2.

814
00:51:32,790 --> 00:51:35,960
I'm Yang Dong Ik, number one.
I'm counting on your vote!

815
00:51:36,230 --> 00:51:37,430
- Hello!
- Sir, you should come by...

816
00:51:37,500 --> 00:51:40,070
- for a check-up.
- Gong Jeong Han, number two.

817
00:51:40,070 --> 00:51:41,870
- Please vote for number two.
- Thank you.

818
00:51:41,940 --> 00:51:43,670
Remember to vote for number one!

819
00:51:44,270 --> 00:51:47,540
- Candidate number two.
- It's organic. I'm Yang Dong Ik.

820
00:51:47,610 --> 00:51:49,440
- Yes, thank you for your support.
- Remember, vote number two.

821
00:51:50,510 --> 00:51:52,680
- Darn it.
- This guy, seriously...

822
00:51:54,080 --> 00:51:57,320
Hello, everyone!
I'm Yang Dong Ik, number one.

823
00:51:57,490 --> 00:51:59,120
With your precious votes...

824
00:51:59,190 --> 00:52:02,120
Please vote for me!
I am candidate number two,

825
00:52:02,360 --> 00:52:03,660
- Gong Jeong Han.
- Gong Jeong Han.

826
00:52:03,730 --> 00:52:04,960
- Gong Jeong Han.
- Gong Jeong Han.

827
00:52:05,390 --> 00:52:07,760
- Number two.
- Hey!

828
00:52:08,160 --> 00:52:09,500
Get lost, all right?

829
00:52:09,600 --> 00:52:12,330
I was here first.
You're the one who cut in.

830
00:52:12,400 --> 00:52:15,840
- Cut in? This little punk...
- "Little punk?"

831
00:52:15,900 --> 00:52:17,510
- That's right, punk.
- Of all the nerve.

832
00:52:17,570 --> 00:52:19,540
- If you had half a brain...
- Seriously...

833
00:52:19,610 --> 00:52:22,410
- Bring it on.
- You two aren't fighting, are you?

834
00:52:22,410 --> 00:52:24,110
- Who's fighting?
- No.

835
00:52:24,280 --> 00:52:26,080
Where did you pop up from?

836
00:52:26,180 --> 00:52:29,680
With both your families in the race,
I've been put on high alert.

837
00:52:29,750 --> 00:52:32,650
I was here campaigning first,

838
00:52:32,850 --> 00:52:35,290
and this man came
and blocked my path.

839
00:52:35,920 --> 00:52:37,990
You think you own this street?

840
00:52:38,060 --> 00:52:39,060
Stop fighting!

841
00:52:39,060 --> 00:52:40,860
I told you. You avoid dog poop
out of disgust, not out of fear.

842
00:52:40,930 --> 00:52:42,730
- Let's go.
- Poop smells scary.

843
00:52:42,730 --> 00:52:44,770
You're running out of fear.

844
00:52:44,830 --> 00:52:46,100
- Hey, Dae Han.
- Yes?

845
00:52:46,170 --> 00:52:47,700
Do you hear a big mutt
barking somewhere?

846
00:52:50,170 --> 00:52:51,540
- Good grief.
- You little piece of...

847
00:52:51,610 --> 00:52:54,780
- Calm down. Everyone's watching.
- Hey, stop.

848
00:52:54,840 --> 00:52:57,850
- Unbelievable.
- Hey, you promised not to fight.

849
00:52:57,910 --> 00:53:01,120
- Yes, you're right. Hello, ma'am!
- Go. Let's go.

850
00:53:01,180 --> 00:53:04,290
- My gosh!
- That jerk! I ought to...

851
00:53:04,420 --> 00:53:08,490
What are you doing?
We must root out these bad people!

852
00:53:08,560 --> 00:53:10,760
Yes. The expert on local commerce
and wellness!

853
00:53:10,830 --> 00:53:14,300
- I'm Yang Dong Ik, number one.
- Gong Jeong Han. Good to see you.

854
00:53:14,360 --> 00:53:17,930
- Right.
- Please. Just one yogurt drink?

855
00:53:18,770 --> 00:53:23,470
How pathetic.
We're giving out herbal health kits.

856
00:53:23,910 --> 00:53:26,270
- Here you go.
- Thank you.

857
00:53:26,610 --> 00:53:28,080
Give one to your chief, too.

858
00:53:28,310 --> 00:53:31,280
- Yes, thank you so much.
- Here, have another one.

859
00:53:31,350 --> 00:53:33,010
- No, that's all right.
- No, I insist. Take them all.

860
00:53:33,050 --> 00:53:35,450
- You really don't have to.
- It's no problem.

861
00:53:35,480 --> 00:53:36,950
- All right, have a good day.
- You, too.

862
00:53:37,020 --> 00:53:39,390
- Have a great day!
- Thank you.

863
00:53:41,090 --> 00:53:43,390
We're even having a guest singer
perform at our event.

864
00:53:43,760 --> 00:53:45,590
You think hiring a singer
will suddenly make you popular?

865
00:53:45,760 --> 00:53:47,030
Sounds like someone's jealous.

866
00:53:47,360 --> 00:53:50,700
I actually went around the market
and polled people.

867
00:53:50,770 --> 00:53:52,130
Every single one of them said
they're voting for us.

868
00:53:52,470 --> 00:53:55,570
- Really?
- Yes, you'll see for yourself. Bye.

869
00:54:01,080 --> 00:54:02,480
Hi, son.

870
00:54:04,510 --> 00:54:07,120
I've been running all over town
looking at apartments for you.

871
00:54:07,720 --> 00:54:10,920
I just popped into a coffee shop
to take a break and have a drink,

872
00:54:11,290 --> 00:54:13,560
and I was wondering
if I could see you for a minute.

873
00:54:14,720 --> 00:54:15,720
Yes.

874
00:54:16,960 --> 00:54:19,260
Okay, I get it.
Good luck with your meeting.

875
00:54:19,830 --> 00:54:21,600
Okay. Have a good day.

876
00:54:36,410 --> 00:54:38,210
- Not bad, right?
- It's nice.

877
00:54:39,050 --> 00:54:41,050
Then you'll turn this way
and exit...

878
00:54:48,260 --> 00:54:50,990
These experts are
really great people.

879
00:55:03,240 --> 00:55:05,870
- Should we do that?
- I like it.

880
00:55:07,080 --> 00:55:08,880
- Good, right?
- Yes.

881
00:55:52,450 --> 00:55:55,360
What's she doing here in Seoul?

882
00:55:56,360 --> 00:55:59,230
- What, you know her?
- What? No.

883
00:56:02,200 --> 00:56:03,470
So you go like this...

884
00:56:05,370 --> 00:56:07,640
Every time sales dropped,
there was...

885
00:56:07,640 --> 00:56:09,600
talk of cuts
in the Fashion Division.

886
00:56:10,000 --> 00:56:12,310
And since we settled for staff cuts
every time,

887
00:56:12,740 --> 00:56:14,180
the only designers left...

888
00:56:15,180 --> 00:56:16,340
are all of you in this room.

889
00:56:18,110 --> 00:56:20,420
If you can't increase sales
next season,

890
00:56:21,480 --> 00:56:23,280
I won't be able to protect you
any longer.

891
00:56:26,820 --> 00:56:28,260
If I may, though.

892
00:56:29,290 --> 00:56:31,630
Is the reason for this drop
in sales...

893
00:56:31,960 --> 00:56:34,800
Is it really fair
to blame it all on the designers?

894
00:56:35,630 --> 00:56:39,730
Even when they reuse old designs
each season with no urgency?

895
00:56:40,540 --> 00:56:44,110
All they ever do is change a button
or move a pocket.

896
00:56:44,540 --> 00:56:47,980
Because even when we come up with
new ideas, at the executive review,

897
00:56:48,040 --> 00:56:50,280
the board always chooses
the safe and uninspired designs.

898
00:56:51,010 --> 00:56:54,120
I looked through the portfolios
of the designers here.

899
00:56:54,480 --> 00:56:58,490
Ms. Kim So Hye, you have a talent
for clever takes on formal designs.

900
00:56:58,950 --> 00:57:03,020
Mr. Jo Seong Min won the top prize
at the Arco Street Competition.

901
00:57:04,090 --> 00:57:08,360
And yet, they repeatedly submit
rehashed, similar designs.

902
00:57:08,600 --> 00:57:12,230
Doesn't that imply the system
is stifling their talents?

903
00:57:14,170 --> 00:57:15,270
And your point is?

904
00:57:18,910 --> 00:57:20,540
Director.

905
00:57:20,640 --> 00:57:23,040
As director of the Fashion Division,

906
00:57:23,040 --> 00:57:25,480
I ask you to please reevaluate
the review system.

907
00:57:27,480 --> 00:57:29,320
And I am also requesting
a budget increase.

908
00:57:38,490 --> 00:57:40,360
I'll discuss it
with the other executives.

909
00:57:50,310 --> 00:57:52,940
Director Yang, are you sure
that was a good idea?

910
00:57:55,540 --> 00:57:58,050
Tell me about it. You don't think
I'm going to get fired, do you?

911
00:57:58,250 --> 00:58:01,220
My stuff from Argentina
hasn't even arrived yet.

912
00:58:06,090 --> 00:58:09,190
Thanks for defending our team,
the ugly duckling of Taehan.

913
00:58:09,260 --> 00:58:10,490
We're truly grateful.

914
00:58:12,190 --> 00:58:13,960
As you all know,

915
00:58:13,960 --> 00:58:16,870
I'm no expert when it comes
to fashion or design.

916
00:58:17,230 --> 00:58:20,240
But I am confident in my ability
to redefine a brand's value,

917
00:58:20,440 --> 00:58:25,170
boost its competitiveness,
and create sustainable growth.

918
00:58:25,940 --> 00:58:28,910
Moving forward, I'll listen to you,
and we'll face challenges together,

919
00:58:29,080 --> 00:58:32,880
so the people wearing your clothes
can be happy.

920
00:58:33,410 --> 00:58:35,980
I'll be right there with you,
working through it all,

921
00:58:36,720 --> 00:58:37,790
and helping in any way I can.

922
00:58:47,200 --> 00:58:50,800
So, on that note, what do you say
to a team dinner tonight?

923
00:58:50,900 --> 00:58:53,000
My gosh. That sounds great!

924
00:58:53,300 --> 00:58:56,400
- Let's go!
- Let's go!

925
00:59:00,310 --> 00:59:01,580
He's the best!

926
00:59:02,380 --> 00:59:03,480
You're the best, Director!

927
00:59:08,050 --> 00:59:12,090
(Sunny Korean Medicine Clinic)

928
00:59:12,150 --> 00:59:13,150
- Dong Suk.
- Hurry, come in.

929
00:59:13,220 --> 00:59:15,020
It's so crowded outside.
What are you doing here?

930
00:59:15,090 --> 00:59:16,930
Hey. Where have you been?

931
00:59:17,060 --> 00:59:20,630
Apartment hunting for Hyun Bin.
Why? I'm sure Dong Ik knows.

932
00:59:20,700 --> 00:59:24,000
It's not that. I heard something.

933
00:59:24,070 --> 00:59:28,270
I was asking around the market.
Everyone's voting for Mr. Gong.

934
00:59:28,470 --> 00:59:33,070
- Is that right?
- "Is that right?" Is that all?

935
00:59:33,170 --> 00:59:35,610
Don't you realize
what a crisis this is?

936
00:59:36,310 --> 00:59:40,150
It seems luck is on our side.

937
00:59:40,250 --> 00:59:42,550
What? Wait,
what's that supposed to mean?

938
00:59:43,280 --> 00:59:45,190
You'll see, Dong Suk.

939
00:59:48,290 --> 00:59:50,290
- Yes.
- Dr. Han.

940
00:59:51,560 --> 00:59:54,230
- You haven't seen it yet, have you?
- Seen what?

941
00:59:54,230 --> 00:59:57,830
The photo of you and Director Song.
It's all over the community forums.

942
00:59:58,470 --> 00:59:59,470
What?

943
01:00:06,310 --> 01:00:10,040
They're saying, "How can a cheater
be an expert on family matters?"

944
01:00:10,480 --> 01:00:13,750
The comments are blowing up,
telling you to leave the show.

945
01:00:19,320 --> 01:00:20,490
Look at this.

946
01:00:21,460 --> 01:00:22,460
Look at this.

947
01:00:22,720 --> 01:00:25,930
What is going on? Don't tell me...

948
01:00:26,360 --> 01:00:27,930
Your wife isn't having an affair,
is she?

949
01:00:29,460 --> 01:00:30,630
Dr. Gong!

950
01:00:30,900 --> 01:00:32,730
The whole market is in an uproar.

951
01:00:32,730 --> 01:00:34,270
They're asking
if Dr. Han is cheating.

952
01:00:34,470 --> 01:00:35,470
For real?

953
01:00:35,740 --> 01:00:38,610
Someone anonymously posted a picture
on the Onjeong Market forum.

954
01:00:38,910 --> 01:00:41,340
They say, "How can he be president
if he can't control his own wife?"

955
01:00:41,640 --> 01:00:42,840
They're saying
you should drop out of the race.

956
01:00:43,310 --> 01:00:45,210
Hey, what about Mom? Does she know?

957
01:00:45,750 --> 01:00:46,750
Probably.

958
01:00:47,050 --> 01:00:49,150
- Oh, no.
- Hey.

959
01:00:49,220 --> 01:00:50,220
Jeong Han!

960
01:00:51,490 --> 01:00:54,490
- You should be fine after two days.
- Okay.

961
01:00:58,190 --> 01:01:02,830
Rumor has it your doctor
daughter-in-law is having an affair.

962
01:01:03,970 --> 01:01:07,940
Oh, goodness, there must be
some kind of misunderstanding.

963
01:01:08,000 --> 01:01:10,670
Your husband ran off
and left you after his affair,

964
01:01:10,770 --> 01:01:13,910
so your daughter-in-law
shouldn't do the same. Right?

965
01:01:14,040 --> 01:01:16,710
Ma'am, that's a misunderstanding.
Really.

966
01:01:17,450 --> 01:01:22,180
Doctor, you need to watch your wife.
When a woman is too successful,

967
01:01:22,480 --> 01:01:24,450
she's bound to cheat.

968
01:01:24,950 --> 01:01:27,320
Oh, Ma'am! Goodness...

969
01:01:27,720 --> 01:01:29,590
Well, I'm leaving.

970
01:01:34,860 --> 01:01:36,230
What is going on?

971
01:01:37,170 --> 01:01:39,500
I don't really know myself.

972
01:01:40,030 --> 01:01:41,400
Good grief.

973
01:01:45,770 --> 01:01:46,970
Oh, Seong Mi.

974
01:01:47,940 --> 01:01:48,980
Yes, Mother.

975
01:01:49,740 --> 01:01:53,650
He's a director I work with.
Jeong Han knows him, too.

976
01:01:54,550 --> 01:01:56,420
We were discussing a TV show...

977
01:01:56,880 --> 01:01:59,120
and looking at reference footage
together.

978
01:02:00,050 --> 01:02:02,120
I guess someone took a picture
and posted it online.

979
01:02:03,290 --> 01:02:05,830
Please, don't you worry about it.
I'm on my way.

980
01:02:06,690 --> 01:02:07,700
Okay.

981
01:02:15,000 --> 01:02:16,240
Hey, Director Song.

982
01:02:17,170 --> 01:02:19,970
This is so ridiculous
I actually have to laugh.

983
01:02:21,340 --> 01:02:22,640
I know, right? Tell me about it.

984
01:02:23,110 --> 01:02:25,050
I'm already getting calls
from reporters.

985
01:02:25,710 --> 01:02:27,580
Anyway, I'll handle it
and clear things up.

986
01:02:28,020 --> 01:02:29,720
Okay, got it.

987
01:02:30,150 --> 01:02:33,150
Listen, Seong Mi.
I was reading the comments, and...

988
01:02:33,920 --> 01:02:35,890
Are you separated from your husband?

989
01:02:37,460 --> 01:02:40,090
No, we just live apart
during the week for work.

990
01:02:40,160 --> 01:02:42,460
The commute's a killer,
so I stay in Seoul.

991
01:02:43,100 --> 01:02:45,270
- Why?
- Well...

992
01:02:45,270 --> 01:02:47,270
The higher-ups
are making it an issue.

993
01:02:47,370 --> 01:02:49,300
They've suddenly told me
to put your contract on hold.

994
01:02:50,300 --> 01:02:53,310
- What?
- I'll call you after my meeting.

995
01:02:53,980 --> 01:02:54,980
Okay.

996
01:02:55,540 --> 01:02:57,410
Of all the crazy things...

997
01:03:03,220 --> 01:03:05,120
Who on earth
could have taken that photo?

998
01:03:08,020 --> 01:03:09,060
What?

999
01:03:12,960 --> 01:03:14,160
It couldn't be...

1000
01:03:17,430 --> 01:03:20,170
It's Jae Geun. You know,
our old classmate Song Jae Geun.

1001
01:03:21,800 --> 01:03:24,940
I know.
I'm not worried about an affair.

1002
01:03:26,410 --> 01:03:27,880
Thanks for that, at least.

1003
01:03:28,110 --> 01:03:30,880
But what about your work?
Is everything okay?

1004
01:03:31,310 --> 01:03:34,020
The network is trying to do
damage control,

1005
01:03:35,650 --> 01:03:37,150
but the contract's been put on hold.

1006
01:03:37,990 --> 01:03:39,850
Oh, man...

1007
01:03:41,020 --> 01:03:43,760
This is exactly why I told you
not to run for the election.

1008
01:03:44,260 --> 01:03:46,260
- What?
- I told you to go for it,

1009
01:03:46,260 --> 01:03:47,760
so I guess it's my own fault.

1010
01:03:49,300 --> 01:03:52,130
Wait, are you saying
this is my fault?

1011
01:03:52,570 --> 01:03:53,670
Yes, I am.

1012
01:03:54,140 --> 01:03:57,170
Yang Dong Ik's wife is the one
who posted that picture.

1013
01:03:57,470 --> 01:04:00,980
- What? Are you sure?
- I'm positive.

1014
01:04:01,280 --> 01:04:04,550
She saw me with Director Song
this afternoon.

1015
01:04:04,710 --> 01:04:07,580
So she saw you two, took a photo,
and posted it just like that?

1016
01:04:07,650 --> 01:04:09,180
Exactly.

1017
01:04:10,320 --> 01:04:14,660
I knew she was something else.
She's completely nuts, isn't she?

1018
01:04:16,020 --> 01:04:17,290
Unbelievable.

1019
01:04:18,030 --> 01:04:21,930
Is she trying to ruin my career
over the stupid merchants' election?

1020
01:04:22,500 --> 01:04:24,470
I am not letting her
get away with this.

1021
01:04:30,810 --> 01:04:32,670
- Beer. Yes, coming right up.
- Thanks.

1022
01:04:32,670 --> 01:04:34,580
- Okay, two, three.
- Thanks for all your hard work.

1023
01:04:34,640 --> 01:04:35,710
Thank you.

1024
01:04:36,440 --> 01:04:38,550
Wow, this meat is great.
It's so good.

1025
01:04:38,610 --> 01:04:40,920
Sir. Over in Argentina,

1026
01:04:40,950 --> 01:04:42,250
what do you say
when you make a toast?

1027
01:04:45,490 --> 01:04:48,920
- Cheers!
- Cheers!

1028
01:04:48,920 --> 01:04:50,660
Bravo!

1029
01:04:50,890 --> 01:04:51,890
All right.

1030
01:04:56,560 --> 01:04:59,500
- That's a good one.
- So good.

1031
01:04:59,570 --> 01:05:03,200
- It really is.
- Drink up. We've had it so rough...

1032
01:05:13,850 --> 01:05:17,920
- Are you drunk?
- A little. I'm just in a good mood.

1033
01:05:18,850 --> 01:05:20,050
And why are you in such a good mood?

1034
01:05:20,820 --> 01:05:24,760
Because you're a nicer person
than I expected.

1035
01:05:26,460 --> 01:05:29,700
I honestly thought you were going to
get revenge on me.

1036
01:05:29,760 --> 01:05:32,300
Man, what kind of person
did you take me for?

1037
01:05:32,730 --> 01:05:35,240
I'm not the kind of guy
who goes around seeking revenge.

1038
01:05:36,200 --> 01:05:37,570
I know, right?

1039
01:05:39,310 --> 01:05:42,780
When you suddenly showed up,
all dressed to the nines,

1040
01:05:42,910 --> 01:05:44,750
you have no idea
how surprised I was.

1041
01:05:47,010 --> 01:05:51,020
And when you made your entrance
with that Hyun Bin theme music,

1042
01:05:51,090 --> 01:05:52,650
that was hilarious.

1043
01:05:54,460 --> 01:05:58,590
Good. I'm glad it landed.
It's a little joke I like to pull.

1044
01:06:00,730 --> 01:06:03,500
I actually know someone
named Hyun Bin, too.

1045
01:06:03,800 --> 01:06:04,800
Yang Hyun Bin.

1046
01:06:06,530 --> 01:06:10,300
We lost touch after he went abroad
a long time ago.

1047
01:06:13,510 --> 01:06:14,510
Is that right?

1048
01:06:15,210 --> 01:06:18,080
That's right. You're a Yang too.

1049
01:06:18,680 --> 01:06:20,410
What's your Korean name?

1050
01:06:26,150 --> 01:06:27,190
Yang Hyun Bin.

1051
01:06:33,930 --> 01:06:38,070
Come on. Stop joking around.
Seriously...

1052
01:06:39,770 --> 01:06:43,800
So what about this Yang Hyun Bin?
Was he your first love or something?

1053
01:06:44,370 --> 01:06:46,870
- No, of course not.
- Really?

1054
01:06:47,580 --> 01:06:51,050
Yes. It would be a disaster
if he were my first love.

1055
01:06:52,610 --> 01:06:53,680
Why is that?

1056
01:06:54,220 --> 01:06:55,420
Because we're enemies.

1057
01:06:57,790 --> 01:06:58,890
Enemies.

1058
01:06:59,420 --> 01:07:02,160
His family and my family...

1059
01:07:02,290 --> 01:07:04,630
are sworn enemies.

1060
01:07:05,090 --> 01:07:07,600
It's a blood feud
passed down through generations.

1061
01:07:17,300 --> 01:07:18,470
Excuse me.

1062
01:07:18,740 --> 01:07:19,740
Honey...

1063
01:07:21,280 --> 01:07:22,310
Me?

1064
01:07:22,940 --> 01:07:27,150
- You told me not to fight.
- Let go. I have nothing to lose.

1065
01:07:28,420 --> 01:07:30,020
No, wait. Hey...

1066
01:07:32,320 --> 01:07:36,860
- Can I help you with something?
- Look at you, playing innocent.

1067
01:07:36,960 --> 01:07:39,990
- Aren't you out of line?
- What? Out of line?

1068
01:07:40,290 --> 01:07:41,360
Who do you think
is out of line here?

1069
01:07:42,330 --> 01:07:44,870
What's with this guy now?
Unbelievable.

1070
01:07:44,930 --> 01:07:48,870
I don't care how desperate you are.
How dare you go after my family?

1071
01:07:48,940 --> 01:07:51,270
My gosh. Excuse me?
What on earth are you talking about?

1072
01:07:51,340 --> 01:07:54,940
- You were in Seoul, weren't you?
- Excuse me? So rude!

1073
01:07:55,010 --> 01:07:57,710
You're the one who took that picture
and posted it, aren't you?

1074
01:07:58,550 --> 01:07:59,610
Do you have any proof?

1075
01:07:59,910 --> 01:08:03,220
- What?
- No, forget it. I'll handle this.

1076
01:08:03,280 --> 01:08:05,890
You can't just accuse someone
without any proof.

1077
01:08:06,350 --> 01:08:08,060
- Let's go.
- The nerve of her...

1078
01:08:08,120 --> 01:08:09,120
- Unbelievable.
- Why, that...

1079
01:08:09,390 --> 01:08:12,890
No, I'll take care of it, okay?
Don't get worked up. Let's go.

1080
01:08:13,790 --> 01:08:16,630
That's enough. Let's go.
Let's go home.

1081
01:08:18,330 --> 01:08:21,070
Seong Mi.

1082
01:08:21,400 --> 01:08:22,770
Seong Mi, hey.

1083
01:08:26,710 --> 01:08:28,440
- My gosh.
- What are you doing?

1084
01:08:30,540 --> 01:08:33,650
- Seong Mi.
- Goodness. I think she's lost it.

1085
01:08:33,680 --> 01:08:35,080
- Seong Mi, you...
- My gosh!

1086
01:08:35,450 --> 01:08:37,820
- You...
- She's crazy! What to do? Hey!

1087
01:08:37,820 --> 01:08:40,350
- What do you think you're doing?
- What's this? A fingerprint?

1088
01:08:40,490 --> 01:08:41,490
Excuse me!

1089
01:08:43,390 --> 01:08:45,830
You just stole my phone, didn't you?

1090
01:08:45,890 --> 01:08:48,800
Seong Mi, just give the phone back
and then we can...

1091
01:08:48,860 --> 01:08:52,070
- My. What are you doing?
- Hey, Han Seong Mi! Let go of her!

1092
01:08:52,130 --> 01:08:53,270
- Let go! My gosh.
- You jerk!

1093
01:08:53,330 --> 01:08:55,940
- You dare touch my wife?
- What? That's hilarious.

1094
01:08:55,940 --> 01:08:57,610
- Hey! What's wrong with you?
- You'd better control your wife!

1095
01:08:57,610 --> 01:08:59,840
- Don't push!
- Get your hands off my wife.

1096
01:08:59,910 --> 01:09:01,910
- Let go!
- Unbelievable.

1097
01:09:30,570 --> 01:09:33,510
(Recipe For Love)

1098
01:09:33,840 --> 01:09:36,010
So, what do you think of her now?
Still into her?

1099
01:09:37,580 --> 01:09:39,950
I may be sitting down right now,

1100
01:09:40,010 --> 01:09:43,780
- but pretend I'm on my knees.
- Crazy witch.

1101
01:09:44,750 --> 01:09:48,220
- What?
- I'm paying for my stepmom's error.

1102
01:09:48,290 --> 01:09:49,760
Have you completely lost your mind?

1103
01:09:50,160 --> 01:09:53,730
- Such a devil's tongue.
- Let's forget this and play fair.

1104
01:09:53,990 --> 01:09:56,900
How could they do this
to such a handsome face?

1105
01:09:57,500 --> 01:09:58,570
It was you, wasn't it?

1106
01:09:59,570 --> 01:10:00,830
You're not going to let this slide,
are you?

1107
01:10:01,640 --> 01:10:02,670
Of course not.
